'''''Rubovietnamia''''' is a genus of plants in the family [[Rubiaceae]], native to [[Vietnam]] and southern [[China]].<ref name="sheilawalsh">Deva D. Tirvengadum. 1998.  Biogeographica: Compte-rendu des seances de la societe de biogeographie, Paris, 74(4): 166â€“168, figs. 4, 5, 6.</ref>

At the present time (May 2014), two species are known:<ref>[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=180459 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families, ''Rubovietnamia'']</ref><ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=317600 Flora of China v 19 p 319, ''Rubovietnamia'']</ref>

*''[[Rubovietnamia aristata]]'' <small>Tirveng. -</small><ref name="sheilawalsh"/> [[Yunnan]], [[Guangxi]], [[Vietnam]]
*''[[Rubovietnamia nonggangensis]]'' <small>F.J.Mou & D.X.Zhang -</small><ref>[http://ejournal.sinica.edu.tw/bbas/content/2010/1/Bot511-14.pdf Feng-Juan Mou & Dian-Xiang Zhang. 2010. ''Rubovietnamia nonggangensis'' (Rubiaceae), a new species from China. Botanical Studies  (Taipei) 51:119-126.]</ref> [[Guangxi]]
*''Rubovietnamia coronula''  Ulrich Meve  - Philippines

